---
import { Image, imageConfig } from "astro:assets";
import Kaleidoscoop from "../img/Kaleidoscoop.png";
import Map from "../img/Map.png";
---

<style>
    .content-wrapper {
        max-width: var(--max-page-width);
        margin-inline: auto;
    }

    h2 {
        margin-block-end: 1rem;
    }

    h3 {
        margin-block-end: 0;
    }

    .grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 40px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 800px) {
        /* Number obtained by manually testing */
        .grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
    }

    p:first-of-type {
        margin-block-start: 0.5rem;
    }

    .tram-D {
        padding: 0.1em 0.5em;
        color: #fff;
        background-color: #009933;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .ter {
        padding: 0.1em 0.5em;
        color: #fff;
        background-color: #0060a1;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .bus-2 {
        padding: 0.1em 0.5em;
        color: #fff;
        background-color: #e10d19;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .apps-row {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 525px) {
        /* Number obtained by manually testing */
        #db-logo {
            display: none;
        }
    }

    .apps-row img {
        margin-block: 2rem;
        border-radius: 0;
        transition: transform 0.05s ease-in;
    }

    .apps-row img:hover {
        transform: scale(1.1);
    }

    ul {
        list-style: none;
        padding-inline-start: 0;
        margin-block-start: 0.3rem;
    }

    li {
        font-size: 1.125rem;
        color: var(--secondary-color);
    }

    .map-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template: repeat(2, auto) / 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 1px;
    }

    .map-grid img {
        grid-column: 1 / -1;
    }

    .map-grid a {
        padding: 1em;
        display: grid;
        place-content: center;
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px #636569;
    }
</style>
<div class="content-wrapper">
    <h2>Getting there</h2>
    <div class="grid">
        <div class="item">
            <h3>The Venue</h3>
            <p>
                The Matrix Conference 2025 will take place at <a
                    href="https://kaleidos.coop">Kaleidoscoop</a
                >, 5 Rue de la Coop√©rative, in Strasbourg, France.
            </p>
            <p>
                We warmly recommend staying in the city center near tram line D
                or bus line 2 to both enjoy the conference and to socialize with
                attendees in the evening!
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <Image src={Kaleidoscoop} alt="" />
        </div>

        <div class="item">
            <div class="map-grid">
                <Image src={Map} alt="" />
                <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/ARex2qD5cH5WoWrE7"
                    >Google Maps</a
                >
                <a
                    href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/directions?to=Kaleidoscoop#map=14/48.57928/7.74888&layers=S"
                    >OpenStreet Map</a
                >
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <h3>Public Transportation</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Tram Line <span class="tram-D">D</span> Get off at "Capitainerie"
                </li>
                <li>
                    Bus line <span class="bus-2">2</span> Get off at "Port du Rhin".
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                You can book a ticket for public transport using the CTS App.
                The app is available in English.
            </p>
            <div class="apps-row">
                <a
                    href="https://apps.apple.com/fr/app/cts-transports-strasbourg/id1241895758"
                    ><img
                        src="/download-app-store.svg"
                        alt="Download CTS on the Apple App Store."
                        width="180"
                        height="60"
                    /></a
                >
                <a
                    href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=fr.cts.strasbourg.ugo"
                    ><img
                        src="/download-google-play.svg"
                        alt="Download CTS on the Google Play Store."
                        width="200"
                        height="60"
                    /></a
                >
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="item">
            <h3>By Train</h3>
            <p>
                Strasbourg is a well connected city. The train station will lead
                you to the city centre, right next to the picturesque
                neighborhood of Petite France. The train station itself is
                connected to Tramway Line <span class="tram-D">D</span> or bus line
                <span class="bus-2">2</span> that lead to the venue.
            </p>
            <div class="apps-row">
                <img
                    id="db-logo"
                    src="/DB_Logo.png"
                    alt="The 'DB' logo of Deutsche Bahn."
                    width="100"
                    height="70"
                />
                <p>
                    The Matrix Conference ticket holders are eligible to use the "<a
                        href="https://www.veranstaltungsticket-bahn.de/?event=35482&language=en"
                        target="_blank">Event Ticket</a>"
                    special offer by Deutsche Bahn to and from the conference!
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <h3>By Plane</h3>
            <p>
                Strasbourg's Airport (SXB) is another option for attendees
                coming from farther. The <span class="ter">TER</span> train connects
                the Airport to Strasbourg's city center in about 30 min. A taxi ride
                will get you there in bout 20 min.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
